          "tab_cQHLrc": {
            "type": "tab",
            "settings": {
              "tab_title": "Refund & Cancellation",
              "tab_content": "<h1><strong>Ludic Kitchen — Refund Policy</strong></h1><p><strong>Issued by:</strong> Good Chaos Lifestyle Pvt. Ltd. (“Ludic”)</p><p>This Refund Policy governs the circumstances under which refunds are issued in connection with Ludic Kitchen Campaigns. This Policy forms an integral part of the <strong>Master Terms & Conditions</strong> and should be read in conjunction with them.</p><h2><strong>1. Core Refund Principle</strong></h2><p>Ludic Kitchen operates on a <strong>campaign-based consumer prepayment model</strong>.<br/>Accordingly:</p><ul><li>Refunds are <strong>not discretionary</strong></li><li>Refunds are governed strictly by <strong>Campaign Activation outcomes</strong></li><li>No refund decisions are made on a case-by-case or subjective basis</li></ul><h2><strong>2. When Refunds Are Permitted</strong></h2><p>Refunds are permitted <strong>only</strong> in the event of <strong>Campaign Non-Activation</strong>.</p><h3><strong>2.1 Definition of Non-Activation</strong></h3><p>A Campaign is classified as <strong>Non-Activated</strong> if:</p><ul><li>The total Contributions received from the community remain <strong>below seventy percent (70%)</strong> of the declared Community Target<br/> <strong>at the time of Campaign Close</strong>.</li></ul><p>In such cases:</p><ul><li>No production begins</li><li>No fulfillment is initiated</li><li>No Campaign benefits are delivered</li></ul><h2><strong>3. Refund Outcomes in Non-Activated Campaigns</strong></h2><p>Where a Campaign is Non-Activated:</p><ul><li>Contributors are eligible for a <strong>full refund of their Contribution</strong>.</li></ul><h2><strong>4. Refund Processing Timeline</strong></h2><ul><li>Refunds are processed within <strong>seven (7) to ten (10) working days</strong> from Campaign Close.</li><li>Refunds are issued to the <strong>original payment method</strong> used at the time of checkout.</li><li>Ludic is not responsible for delays caused by:</li><li>Banking institutions</li><li>Payment gateways</li><li>Card issuers or wallet providers<br/><br/></li></ul><h2><strong>5. When Refunds Are Not Permitted</strong></h2><p>Refunds are <strong>not permitted</strong> in any of the following circumstances:</p><h3><strong>5.1 Post-Activation</strong></h3><ul><li>Once a Campaign is <strong>Activated (≥70%)</strong>, all Contributions become <strong>confirmed consumer prepayments</strong>.</li><li>No refunds, partial refunds, or adjustments are permitted after Activation, regardless of:</li><li>Whether Activation occurs early or late</li><li>Whether the Contributor has received products or Ludic Credits</li><li>Personal circumstances or change of mind<br/><br/></li></ul><h3><strong>5.2 Change of Mind or Personal Reasons</strong></h3><p>Refunds are not issued for reasons including, but not limited to:</p><ul><li>Change of preference</li><li>Delay expectations</li><li>Styling or aesthetic dissatisfaction</li><li>Personal emergencies or financial constraints</li><li>Inability to use or redeem benefits<br/><br/></li></ul><h3><strong>5.3 Tier or Seat-Related Reasons</strong></h3><ul><li>No refunds are permitted due to:</li><li>Tier closures</li><li>Inability to downgrade or switch tiers</li><li>Inability to upgrade due to unavailability<br/><br/></li></ul><h2><strong>6. No Cancellations After Contribution</strong></h2><ul><li>Once a Contribution is successfully completed:</li><li>The Seat is allocated</li><li>The Contribution is locked</li><li>Contributions <strong>cannot be cancelled, reversed, or withdrawn</strong> after checkout.</li></ul><p>This lock-in is essential to preserve production planning, pricing integrity, and campaign fairness.</p><h2><strong>7. Chargebacks & Unauthorized Refund Attempts</strong></h2><ul><li>Unauthorized chargebacks or payment disputes initiated after a successful Contribution may result in:</li><li>Immediate suspension of the associated account</li><li>Invalidation of the allocated Seat</li><li>Disqualification from current and future Ludic Kitchen Campaigns</li><li>Ludic reserves the right to contest chargebacks where Campaign access, benefits, or fulfillment processes have commenced.<br/><br/></li></ul><h2><strong>8. Refunds vs Exchanges (Important Distinction)</strong></h2><ul><li>Refunds apply only to Contributions made to Non-Activated Campaigns.</li><li>For Product-related issues (including defects or damage), customers are eligible for an exchange only, not a refund.</li><li>All exchange requests must be raised within <strong>7 days of receiving the product</strong>.</li></ul><h2><strong>9. Statutory Consumer Rights</strong></h2><p>Nothing in this Refund Policy limits or excludes rights available to consumers under applicable Indian law.</p><p><strong>Statutory consumer rights remain unaffected</strong>, including rights related to defective, damaged, or misrepresented goods where applicable.</p><h2><strong>10. Finality of Refund Decisions</strong></h2><ul><li>Refund decisions made in accordance with this Policy are final and binding.</li><li>Ludic does not offer discretionary or goodwill refunds beyond what is expressly stated herein.</li></ul><h2><strong>11. Support & Queries</strong></h2><p>For refund-related queries:</p><p><strong>Email:</strong> kitchen@ludic.life<br/><strong>Response Time:</strong> Acknowledgment within 24–48 hours</p>"
            }
          },
          "tab_EkhLWj": {
            "type": "tab",
            "settings": {
              "tab_title": "Ludic Credit",
              "tab_content": "<h1><strong>Ludic Kitchen — Credit Policy</strong></h1><p><strong>Issued by:</strong> Good Chaos Lifestyle Pvt. Ltd. (“Ludic”)</p><p>This Credit Policy governs the issuance, validity, usage, and treatment of <strong>Ludic Credit</strong> issued in connection with Ludic Kitchen Campaigns. This Policy forms an integral part of the <strong>Master Terms of Use</strong> and should be read in conjunction with them.</p><h2><strong>1. What is Ludic Credit?</strong></h2><p>Ludic Credit is a <strong>closed-loop store credit</strong> issued by Ludic to Contributors as part of select Ludic Kitchen Campaigns.</p><ul><li>Ludic Credit represents <strong>future purchase value</strong>, not cash.</li><li>It is usable <strong>only within Ludic’s official ecosystem</strong>.</li><li>Ludic Credit is <strong>not</strong>:</li><li>Legal tender</li><li>A wallet balance</li><li>A prepaid payment instrument requiring RBI authorization</li><li>An investment or financial return</li></ul><p>Ludic Credit exists solely to ensure that every eligible Contribution retains full monetary value within the Ludic ecosystem.</p><h2><strong>2. Eligibility for Ludic Credit</strong></h2><ul><li>Ludic Credit is issued <strong>only for tiers explicitly marked as credit-eligible</strong> on the Campaign page.</li><li>Not all tiers may include Ludic Credit as a benefit.</li><li>Credit eligibility, value, and conditions are disclosed prior to Contribution.</li></ul><p>Once a Contribution is completed, credit eligibility <strong>cannot be changed or upgraded</strong>.</p><h2><strong>3. Credit Issuance Timing</strong></h2><ul><li>Ludic Credit is issued <strong>within ten (10) business days</strong> following Campaign Close.</li><li>Credit issuance occurs:</li><li>Only for <strong>Activated Campaigns</strong>.</li><li>Credit issuance is <strong>independent of product delivery</strong> and fulfillment timelines.<br/><br/></li></ul><h2><strong>4. Credit Value</strong></h2><ul><li>The value of Ludic Credit issued corresponds exactly to the Contribution amount applicable to the Contributor’s tier.</li><li>Ludic Credit:</li><li>Does not earn interest</li><li>Does not appreciate or depreciate</li><li>Is not subject to adjustment post-issuance</li></ul><p>The credit value is fixed and final upon issuance.</p><h2><strong>5. Credit Validity & Expiry</strong></h2><ul><li>Ludic Credit is valid for the period specified in the applicable Campaign Terms or on the respective Campaign page for that project.</li><li>Any unused credit will automatically expire at the end of the stated validity period.</li><li>Expired credit:</li><li>cannot be reinstated</li><li>cannot be refunded</li><li>cannot be transferred</li><li>cannot be converted into cash or any other form of value</li><li>Contributors are responsible for tracking their credit validity and usage.</li></ul><h2><strong>6. Credit Usage Rules</strong></h2><ul><li>Ludic Credit may be redeemed <strong>only against the product value</strong> of purchases made on Ludic’s official platforms.</li><li>Unless expressly stated otherwise:</li><li>Ludic Credit must be redeemed in <strong>a single transaction</strong></li><li>Partial redemption across multiple orders is <strong>not permitted</strong></li></ul><p>If the purchase value exceeds the credit value, the balance must be paid separately.</p><h2><strong>7. Non-Transferability & Account Restrictions</strong></h2><ul><li>Ludic Credit is:</li><li>Linked exclusively to the Contributor’s registered account</li><li>Non-transferable</li><li>Non-assignable</li><li>Credit may not be:</li><li>Sold</li><li>Gifted</li><li>Shared</li><li>Combined across multiple accounts</li><li>Any attempt to misuse or transfer credit may result in forfeiture of the remaining credit and suspension of the account.<br/><br/></li></ul><h2><strong>8. Credit in Case of Refunds or Non-Activation</strong></h2><ul><li>In the event of Campaign Non-Activation:</li><li>Contributors may receive a refund, as disclosed on the Campaign page.</li><li>Once Ludic Credit is issued:</li><li>It replaces the monetary value of the Contribution</li><li>No cash refund may be claimed in lieu of issued credit</li></ul><h2><strong>9. Accounting & Tax Treatment (Informational)</strong></h2><ul><li>Ludic Credit is recorded by Ludic as <strong>deferred revenue</strong> until redemption.</li><li>Goods and Services Tax (GST) shall be charged in accordance with applicable GST laws.</li><li>Tax invoices are issued in compliance with applicable law.</li></ul><p>This section is provided for transparency and does not constitute financial or tax advice.</p><h2><strong>10. Suspension, Forfeiture & Misuse</strong></h2><p>Ludic reserves the right to suspend or forfeit Ludic Credit where:</p><ul><li>Fraudulent activity is detected</li><li>Credit is obtained or used in violation of these Terms</li><li>Account misuse or policy breach occurs</li></ul><p>Such action may be taken without liability, subject to applicable law.</p><h2><strong>11. Modification of Credit Program</strong></h2><ul><li>Ludic reserves the right to modify Ludic Credit mechanics for <strong>future Campaigns</strong>.</li><li>Changes will <strong>not</strong> affect:</li><li>Credits already issued</li><li>Validity periods already in force</li></ul><h2><strong>12. No Cash Equivalent or Financial Right</strong></h2><ul><li>Ludic Credit:</li><li>Has no cash value</li><li>Creates no entitlement to refunds</li><li>Does not constitute a financial instrument</li><li>Issuance of Ludic Credit does not create a banking, fiduciary, or custodial relationship.</li></ul><h2><strong>13. Support & Queries</strong></h2><p>For credit-related queries:</p><p><strong>Email:</strong> kitchen@ludic.life<br/><strong>Response Time:</strong> Acknowledgment within 24–48 hours</p>"
            }
          },
          "tab_G3f4eq": {
            "type": "tab",
            "settings": {
              "tab_title": "Privacy Policy",
              "tab_content": "<h1><strong>Ludic Kitchen — Privacy Policy</strong></h1><p><strong>Issued by:</strong> Good Chaos Lifestyle Pvt. Ltd. (“Ludic”)</p><h2><strong>1. Introduction</strong></h2><p>Welcome to Ludic.</p><p>At Ludic, we believe transparency isn’t just for how we make products — it’s also for how we handle your information. When you share your details with us, you’re trusting us to use them responsibly and respectfully. We take that seriously.</p><p>This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Good Chaos Lifestyle Pvt. Ltd. (“Ludic”, “we”, “us”, or “our”)</strong> collects, uses, stores, shares, and protects your personal information when you:</p><ul><li>visit our website or digital platforms</li><li>create a Ludic account</li><li>participate in Ludic Kitchen campaigns</li><li>make purchases or contributions</li><li>interact with us for support, events, or community engagement</li></ul><p>This Policy applies to all information collected through our official platforms and in connection with Ludic products and Ludic Kitchen campaigns.</p><p>In simple terms, this document explains:</p><ul><li>what information we collect</li><li>why we collect it</li><li>how we use it</li><li>who we share it with</li><li>and the choices available to you</li></ul><p>By accessing or using our platform or participating in a campaign, you agree to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.</p><p>If you have any questions about how your information is handled, you can write to us at <a href=\"mailto:kitchen@ludic.life\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>kitchen@ludic.life</strong></span></a></p><h2><strong>2. Information We Collect</strong></h2><p>We collect only the information necessary to run Ludic smoothly, fulfill your orders or contributions, and keep you informed about your participation in Ludic Kitchen.</p><p>Depending on how you interact with us, we may collect the following types of information:</p><h3><strong>2.1 Information You Provide Directly</strong></h3><p>This includes details you voluntarily share with us when creating an account, making a purchase or contribution, or contacting us.</p><p>Examples include:</p><ul><li>Full name</li><li>Email address</li><li>Phone number</li><li>Profile Image</li><li>Billing and shipping address</li><li>Size or fit preferences (for products)</li><li>Account login details</li><li>Campaign selections, votes, feedback, or submissions</li><li>Messages or queries sent to customer support</li><li>Event or community participation details (where applicable)</li></ul><p>You may choose not to provide certain information, but this may limit your ability to participate in campaigns or receive products.</p><h3><strong>2.2 Payment Information</strong></h3><p>When you make a purchase or contribution, payments are processed through secure third-party payment gateways.</p><p>Ludic does not store or have access to your card numbers, bank account details, or wallet credentials.</p><p>We only receive limited confirmation details such as:</p><ul><li>payment status</li><li>transaction ID</li><li>payment method type</li></ul><p>This helps us verify and record your contribution.</p><h3><strong>2.3 Information Collected Automatically</strong></h3><p>When you use our website or platform, certain information is collected automatically to help us operate, secure, and improve the experience.</p><p>This may include:</p><ul><li>Device type and browser information</li><li>IP address</li><li>Pages visited and time spent</li><li>Date and time of visits</li><li>Referring links</li><li>Basic usage analytics</li><li>Cookies and similar tracking technologies</li></ul><p>This information helps us understand what’s working, fix issues, and make Ludic easier to use.</p><h3><strong>2.4 Information from Community Interactions</strong></h3><p>If you choose to engage with Ludic through:</p><ul><li>reviews</li><li>testimonials</li><li>surveys</li><li>photos or videos you share with us</li><li>social media tags or mentions</li></ul><p>we may collect and use that content in accordance with this Privacy Policy or with your permission.</p><p>Participation in these activities is always voluntary.<br/><br/></p><p>We collect only what is relevant and necessary. We do not intentionally collect sensitive personal information that is unrelated to your participation with Ludic.</p><h2><strong>3. How We Use Your Information</strong></h2><p>We use your information only for clear, necessary purposes related to operating Ludic, fulfilling your orders or contributions, and improving your experience with us.</p><p>We do not sell your personal information or use it for unrelated advertising.</p><p>Depending on how you interact with Ludic, your information may be used in the following ways:</p><h3><strong>3.1 To Create and Manage Your Account</strong></h3><ul><li>Register your account</li><li>Log you in securely</li><li>Maintain your profile and preferences</li><li>Provide access to your orders, contributions, and Ludic Credits</li></ul><h3><strong>3.2 To Process Purchases and Contributions</strong></h3><ul><li>Confirm and record your orders or campaign contributions</li><li>Allocate Seats and tiers</li><li>Process payments through secure payment partners</li><li>Generate invoices and transaction confirmations</li><li>Issue Ludic Credits (where applicable)</li></ul><h3><strong>3.3 To Fulfill Products and Deliver Orders</strong></h3><ul><li>Ship products to your address</li><li>Coordinate deliveries through logistics partners</li><li>Share tracking updates</li><li>Handle exchanges or product-related support</li></ul><h3><strong>3.4 To Communicate With You</strong></h3><ul><li>Send campaign updates and milestone announcements</li><li>Notify you about Activation, fulfillment, or credit issuance</li><li>Respond to your questions or support requests</li><li>Share important policy or account-related notices</li></ul><p>These communications are essential to your participation in Ludic Kitchen.</p><h3><strong>3.5 To Improve Our Platform and Experience</strong></h3><ul><li>Understand how visitors use our website</li><li>Fix bugs or technical issues</li><li>Improve design, usability, and performance</li><li>Plan future products and campaigns based on aggregated insights</li></ul><p>This analysis is typically done using anonymized or aggregated data wherever possible.</p><h3><strong>3.6 To Support Community & Creative Participation</strong></h3><ul><li>Record votes, feedback, and submissions</li><li>Recognize contributors (where applicable)</li><li>Evaluate ideas for future Ludic products or campaigns</li><li>Manage events or community initiatives</li></ul><p>Participation in these activities is always optional.</p><h3><strong>3.7 To Comply With Legal and Regulatory Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li>Maintain accounting and tax records</li><li>Prevent fraud or misuse</li><li>Enforce our Terms of Use</li><li>Respond to lawful requests from authorities</li></ul><p>We use your information only for the purposes described above and only to the extent necessary. We do not use your data for profiling, reselling, or unrelated third-party marketing.</p><h2><strong>4. How We Share Your Information</strong></h2><p>We treat your personal information with care and discretion.</p><p>We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal data to advertisers, data brokers, or unrelated third parties.</p><p>We share your information only when it is necessary to operate Ludic, fulfill your orders or contributions, or comply with legal obligations.</p><p>Depending on your interaction with us, we may share limited information with the following categories of partners:</p><h3><strong>4.1 Payment Partners</strong></h3><p>To securely process purchases and campaign contributions, we work with trusted third-party payment gateways.</p><p>They receive only the information required to:</p><ul><li>process transactions</li><li>verify payments</li><li>prevent fraud</li></ul><p>Ludic does not store your card numbers, bank details, or wallet credentials.</p><h3><strong>4.2 Logistics & Delivery Partners</strong></h3><p>To ship products and fulfill orders, we share necessary delivery information with logistics providers, such as:</p><ul><li>your name</li><li>shipping address</li><li>phone number (for delivery coordination)</li></ul><p>This information is used solely for delivering your order.</p><h3><strong>4.3 Technology & Platform Providers</strong></h3><p>We use third-party tools and service providers to help operate our website and systems, including:</p><ul><li>hosting and cloud infrastructure</li><li>analytics tools</li><li>customer support software</li><li>email and communication services</li></ul><p>These partners process information only on our behalf and are contractually required to protect your data.</p><h3><strong>4.4 Legal & Regulatory Authorities</strong></h3><p>We may disclose information where required to:</p><ul><li>comply with applicable laws or legal processes</li><li>respond to lawful government or regulatory requests</li><li>enforce our Terms of Use</li><li>prevent fraud, abuse, or security risks</li></ul><p>Such disclosures are made only when legally necessary.</p><h3><strong>4.5 Business Transfers (If Applicable)</strong></h3><p>If Ludic undergoes a merger, acquisition, restructuring, or sale of assets, user information may be transferred as part of that process.</p><p>In such cases, your data will continue to be protected under this Privacy Policy or an equivalent standard.</p><p><br/>Outside of the situations described above, we do not share your personal information with third parties.</p><h2><strong>5. Cookies & Tracking Technologies</strong></h2><p>Like most websites, Ludic uses cookies and similar technologies to make our platform work smoothly and improve your experience.</p><p>Cookies are small text files stored on your device that help us remember preferences and understand how our website is used.</p><h3><strong>5.1 What We Use Cookies For</strong></h3><p>We use cookies to:</p><ul><li>keep you logged into your account</li><li>remember your preferences and settings</li><li>enable secure checkout and contributions</li><li>understand how visitors use our website</li><li>improve performance and fix issues</li></ul><p>These cookies help us operate the platform efficiently and make Ludic easier to use.</p><h3><strong>5.2 Analytics</strong></h3><p>We may use trusted analytics tools to collect aggregated, non-identifiable information such as:</p><ul><li>pages visited</li><li>time spent on the site</li><li>general location (city-level)</li><li>device or browser type</li></ul><p>This helps us understand what’s working and how we can improve the experience.</p><p>We do not use this data to personally identify you.</p><h3><strong>5.3 Your Choices</strong></h3><p>Most browsers allow you to control or disable cookies through settings.</p><p>You may:</p><ul><li>delete existing cookies</li><li>block certain cookies</li><li>set alerts before cookies are stored</li></ul><p>Please note that disabling cookies may affect certain features of the website, such as login, checkout, or campaign participation.</p><p>We use cookies thoughtfully and only to support functionality, security, and improvement — not for selling your data or intrusive tracking.</p><h2><strong>6. Data Retention</strong></h2><p>We retain your personal information only for as long as it is necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy.</p><p>The retention period depends on the type of information and your interaction with Ludic.</p><h3><strong>6.1 Account Information</strong></h3><p>If you create a Ludic account, we retain your basic account information for as long as your account remains active.</p><p>If you choose to delete your account, we will delete or anonymize your personal data, except where retention is required for legal, tax, or regulatory purposes.</p><h3><strong>6.2 Orders & Contributions</strong></h3><p>Information related to purchases, campaign contributions, invoices, and Ludic Credits may be retained for longer periods to:</p><ul><li>comply with tax and accounting laws</li><li>maintain financial records</li><li>resolve disputes</li><li>enforce agreements</li></ul><p>This retention is required under applicable Indian laws and business regulations.</p><h3><strong>6.3 Communication Records</strong></h3><p>If you contact customer support or participate in community initiatives, we may retain those records for a reasonable period to:</p><ul><li>address follow-up requests</li><li>improve customer experience</li><li>maintain service quality</li></ul><h3><strong>6.4 Analytics & Technical Data</strong></h3><p>Certain usage and analytics data may be retained in aggregated or anonymized form for performance improvement and business planning.</p><p>Anonymized data does not identify you personally.</p><p>Once your information is no longer required for legitimate business or legal purposes, we securely delete, anonymize, or restrict access to it.</p><p>We do not retain personal data indefinitely without purpose.</p><h2><strong>7. Your Rights & Choices</strong></h2><p>We believe your information belongs to you.</p><p>You have control over how your personal data is used, and we aim to make it easy for you to access, update, or manage your information at any time.</p><p>Depending on your interaction with Ludic, you may have the following rights:</p><h3><strong>7.1 Access Your Information</strong></h3><p>You may request a copy of the personal information we hold about you, including details about how it is being used.</p><h3><strong>7.2 Correct or Update Your Information</strong></h3><p>You can update or correct your personal details at any time through your account settings or by contacting us.</p><p>Keeping your information accurate helps us fulfill your orders and communicate with you properly.</p><h3><strong>7.3 Delete Your Information</strong></h3><p>You may request deletion of your personal data or account.</p><p>Upon request, we will delete or anonymize your information, except where retention is required for:</p><ul><li>legal or tax obligations</li><li>accounting records</li><li>fraud prevention</li><li>dispute resolution</li></ul><h3><strong>7.4 Withdraw Consent</strong></h3><p>Where we rely on your consent to process information (such as optional communications or community participation), you may withdraw that consent at any time.</p><p>This will not affect processing already completed.</p><h3><strong>7.5 Opt Out of Marketing Communications</strong></h3><p>You can unsubscribe from non-essential emails at any time by:</p><ul><li>clicking the “unsubscribe” link in emails, or</li><li>contacting us directly</li></ul><p>Please note that you will still receive important transactional or campaign-related updates necessary for your participation.</p><h3><strong>7.6 Raise Concerns or Complaints</strong></h3><p>If you believe your information has been used improperly or you have concerns about your privacy, you can contact us and we will address the issue promptly.</p><p>We take privacy concerns seriously and aim to resolve them quickly and fairly.</p><h3>How to Exercise Your Rights</h3><p>To make any request related to your data, simply email us at: <br/>kitchen@ludic.life</p><p>We typically acknowledge requests within 24–48 hours and aim to resolve them within a reasonable timeframe.</p><p><br/><br/>We want you to feel confident and in control when interacting with Ludic. If something doesn’t feel right, just reach out — we’re here to help.</p><h2><strong>8. Data Security</strong></h2><p>We take the security of your personal information seriously and use reasonable safeguards to protect it from unauthorized access, misuse, loss, or disclosure.</p><p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures, including:</p><ul><li>secure servers and hosting environments</li><li>encrypted connections (HTTPS)</li><li>restricted access to sensitive information</li><li>role-based internal access controls</li><li>trusted third-party service providers</li><li>regular monitoring of our systems</li></ul><p>Access to personal information is limited only to team members or partners who need it to operate Ludic, fulfill orders, or provide support.</p><h3><strong>Payment Security</strong></h3><p>All payments and contributions are processed through certified third-party payment gateways.</p><p>Ludic does not store your card numbers, bank details, or wallet credentials on our servers.</p><h3><strong>A Realistic Note</strong></h3><p>While we take strong precautions, no online system can be completely secure.</p><p>If we ever become aware of a security issue affecting your personal data, we will take prompt steps to investigate, contain, and notify affected users as required by law.</p><p><br/>Protecting your trust is as important to us as creating great products, and we continuously work to keep your information safe.</p><h2><strong>9. Third-Party Links & Services</strong></h2><p>Our website or communications may sometimes include links to third-party websites, platforms, or services, such as payment gateways, logistics partners, social media platforms, or external tools.</p><p>These third-party platforms operate independently and have their own privacy policies and practices.</p><p>Once you leave Ludic’s website or interact directly with a third-party service, this Privacy Policy no longer applies.</p><p>We encourage you to review the privacy policies of those third parties before sharing your information with them.</p><p>Ludic is not responsible for the content, security, or privacy practices of external websites or services that we do not control.</p><h2><strong>10. Changes to This Privacy Policy</strong></h2><p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices, technology, legal requirements, or the way Ludic operates.</p><p>When we make material changes, we will:</p><ul><li>notify users through our website, email, or other appropriate communication channels where necessary</li></ul><p>Updated policies take effect once published on our platform.</p><p>We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically to stay informed about how your information is handled.</p><p>Your continued use of Ludic’s platform or participation in campaigns after any updates constitutes acceptance of the revised Privacy Policy.</p><h2><strong>11. Contact & Grievance Redressal</strong></h2><p>If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or how your personal information is handled, please feel free to reach out to us.</p><p>We’re happy to help.</p><p>Support & Privacy Contact<br/>Email: kitchen@ludic.life<br/>Phone: +91 72270 14632</p><p>Response Timelines</p><ul><li>Acknowledgment: within 24–48 hours</li><li>Resolution: within 7 business days, where feasible</li></ul><p>If you wish to:</p><ul><li>access or update your information</li><li>request deletion of your data</li><li>withdraw consent</li><li>report a privacy concern</li><li>or raise a grievance</li></ul><p>simply email us, and our team will assist you promptly.</p><p>We aim to resolve all concerns fairly, transparently, and with care.</p>"
            }
