              "tab_title": "Campaign Terms",
              "tab_content": "<h1><strong>Ludic Kitchen — Campaign Terms<br/>Project 01: Ludic Clogs</strong></h1><p><strong>Issued by:</strong> Good Chaos Lifestyle Pvt. Ltd. (“Ludic”)</p><h1><strong>1. Introduction & Scope</strong></h1><p>These Campaign Terms describe the specific rules, mechanics, timelines, and participation details for <strong>Ludic Kitchen — Project 01: Ludic Clogs</strong> (the “Campaign”).</p><p>While Ludic Kitchen operates on a shared philosophy of transparency and co-creation, each project may have its own structure, duration, tiers, perks, and timelines. This document exists to clearly explain how <strong>this particular Campaign</strong> works.</p><p>It covers details such as:</p><ul><li>campaign duration and milestones</li><li>tier structure and seat allocation</li><li>contribution mechanics</li><li>activation rules</li><li>production and fulfillment timelines</li><li>perks and rewards included in each tier</li></ul><p>These Campaign Terms apply <strong>in addition to</strong> the following documents:</p><ul><li>Master Terms of Use</li><li>Refund Policy</li><li>Credit Policy</li><li>Privacy Policy</li></ul><p>By participating in this Campaign, you agree to be bound by all of the above.</p><p>If there is any conflict between these Campaign Terms and the Master Terms, these Campaign Terms will apply only to the extent of the specific Campaign mechanics described here. All other legal rights and obligations remain governed by the Master Terms & Policies.</p><h1><strong>2. About Ludic Kitchen</strong></h1><p>Ludic Kitchen is Ludic’s community-powered way of creating products.</p><p>Instead of developing products behind closed doors and launching them fully finished, we open up the process and invite our community to take part early — from idea to production.</p><p>Each Kitchen project follows a simple flow:</p><ol><li>We introduce a product concept</li><li>The community backs it by choosing a tier and contributing</li><li>Design and development happen transparently</li><li>Once the minimum goal is reached, production begins</li><li>Contributors receive the product and any included perks or Ludic Credit</li></ol><p>Your contribution is not an investment or donation.<br/> It is an <strong>advance purchase that helps bring the product to life</strong>.</p><p>If a project reaches its activation threshold, we proceed with production and fulfillment.<br/>If it does not, contributions are refunded as described in the Refund Policy.</p><p>In short, Ludic Kitchen is built to be:</p><ul><li>collaborative</li><li>transparent</li><li>low-risk</li><li>and community-led</li></ul><p>You don’t just buy the final product — you help make it happen</p><h1><strong>3. Campaign Snapshot (Quick Facts)</strong></h1><p>Below is a summary of the key details for <strong>Ludic Kitchen — Project 01: Ludic Clogs</strong>.<br/><br/><strong>Campaign Details</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Campaign Name:</strong> Project 01 — Ludic Clogs</li><li><strong>Product:</strong> Ludic Clogs</li><li><strong>Campaign Duration:</strong> 60 days</li><li><strong>Campaign Launch Date:</strong> [Insert date]</li><li><strong>Campaign Close Date:</strong> [Insert date]</li><li><strong>Participation:</strong> Limited seats available; first-come, first-served</li></ul><p><br/><br/></p><h3><strong>Tier Pricing</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>T1:</strong> ₹2,500</li><li><strong>T2:</strong> ₹5,000</li><li><strong>T3:</strong> ₹10,000<br/><br/></li></ul><h3><strong>Early Bird</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>Early Bird Window:</strong> First 15 days</li><li><strong>Early Bird Benefit:</strong> 20% discount on tier price (perks remain identical)<br/><br/></li></ul><h3><strong>Production & Fulfilment</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>Production Start:</strong> Begins only after Activation</li><li><strong>Estimated Fulfilment Window:</strong> 8-10 weeks after Campaign Close<br/><br/></li></ul><h3><strong>Ludic Credit</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>T2 Ludic Credit:</strong> ₹5,000 (Valid for 6 months)</li><li><strong>T3 Ludic Credit:</strong> ₹10,000 (Valid for 12 months)<br/><br/></li></ul><p><strong>Funding Structure<br/><br/>Project Funding Breakdown</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Total Project Cost: </strong>₹75,00,000</li><li><strong>Ludic Contribution (Brand Pledge): </strong>₹15,00,000</li><li><strong>Community Target: </strong>₹60,00,000<strong><br/><br/></strong></li></ul><h3><strong>Activation Rules</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>Activation Threshold: </strong>75% of Community Target (₹45,00,000)</li><li><strong>Brand Top-Up Range: </strong>70–74% (at Ludic’s discretion)</li><li><strong>Non-Activation: </strong>Below 70% → refunds or Ludic Credit issued<strong><br/><br/></strong></li></ul><h3><strong>Important Notes</strong></h3><ul><li>Ludic commits capital upfront before inviting the community to participate.</li><li>The Campaign runs for the full 60 days and does not close early upon reaching the goal.</li><li>Seats are limited and may close as tiers fill.</li><li>All timelines are estimates and may vary due to production or operational factors.</li></ul><h1><strong>4. Tier Structure & Seat Allocation</strong></h1><p>Participation in Ludic Kitchen happens through a <strong>seat-based system</strong>.</p><p>Each contribution secures one “Seat” in the Campaign and determines your tier, benefits, and level of involvement.</p><h3><strong>4.1 What is a Seat?</strong></h3><p>A Seat represents:</p><ul><li>one confirmed participation in the Campaign</li><li>one selected tier</li><li>one set of associated products, perks, and benefits</li></ul><p>Your Seat is secured once your contribution payment is successfully completed.</p><h3><strong>4.2 How Seats Are Allocated</strong></h3><p>Seats are:</p><ul><li>allocated on a first-come, first-served basis</li><li>confirmed only after successful payment</li></ul><p>Adding a tier to your cart or beginning checkout does not reserve a Seat.</p><p>Your participation is confirmed only after payment is completed.</p><h3><strong>4.3 One Seat Per Account</strong></h3><p>Each registered account may hold one Seat per tier purchase.<br/>Seats are linked to the contributing account and cannot be shared across multiple accounts.</p><h3><strong>4.4 Non-Transferability</strong></h3><p>Seats are:</p><ul><li>non-transferable</li><li>non-assignable</li><li>cannot be resold, gifted, or exchanged</li></ul><p>This ensures fairness and protects campaign planning and fulfillment accuracy.</p><h3><strong>4.5 Tier Availability & Closures</strong></h3><p>Each tier has limited availability.</p><p>When a tier reaches capacity:</p><ul><li>that tier may close automatically</li><li>other tiers may remain open</li></ul><p>Closure of a tier does not mean the Campaign has ended.</p><h3><strong>4.6 Campaign Duration Integrity</strong></h3><p>The Campaign runs for the full <strong>60-day duration</strong>.</p><p>The Campaign does not close early due to:</p><ul><li>reaching the Community Target</li><li>achieving Activation</li><li>early success or overfunding</li></ul><p>Contributions may continue until the official Campaign Close date, subject to seat availability.</p><h3><strong>4.7 Tier Changes</strong></h3><p>Once a contribution is completed:</p><ul><li>Tiers may be upgraded, subject to availability and applicable additional charges.</li><li>Tier downgrades are not permitted.</li></ul><p>This lock-in is necessary to maintain production planning and fairness for all participants.</p><h1><strong>5. Contributions & What You Receive</strong></h1><p>To participate in this Campaign, you select a tier and complete the corresponding payment.</p><p>Your contribution is treated as an <strong>advance purchase</strong> that helps fund the creation and production of the Ludic Kitchen Product.</p><p>Once payment is successful:</p><ul><li>your Seat in the Campaign is confirmed</li><li>your selected tier is locked</li><li>you become eligible to receive the product and the perks assigned to that tier</li></ul><p>Contributions are not investments or ownership in Ludic and do not provide financial returns or profit-sharing.</p><p>Specific perks are described in the <strong>Perk Definitions</strong> section below, with a complete tier-wise breakdown in the <strong>Tier Benefits Overview</strong>.<br/><br/></p><h1><strong>6. Perks & Rewards (Project 01)</strong></h1><p>The following perks apply to Project 01: Ludic Clogs.<br/> Availability varies by tier (Taster, Sous Chef, Head Chef) as indicated in the Tier Benefits Overview.</p><p>Each perk is explained below for clarity.</p><h3><strong>1. Ludic Clogs</strong></h3><p>The final production version of the product created through Project 01.</p><p>Delivered after the Campaign concludes and production is complete.<br/>The product reflects the final outcome of the community-backed development process.</p><p>Minor changes from early visuals, prototypes, or concept images may occur due to manufacturing feasibility, material sourcing, or quality refinement.</p><h3><strong>2. Recipe Card</strong></h3><p>A small printed insert included with your Project 01 delivery that documents the story behind the product.</p><p>The Recipe Card typically includes:</p><ul><li>the idea or concept behind the project</li><li>materials or construction highlights</li><li>key design decisions or notes from the process</li></ul><p>It serves as a keepsake that captures how the product came to life and the journey the community helped shape.</p><p>The Recipe Card is informational and commemorative in nature.<br/>It is not a manual, warranty document, or detailed technical specification.<br/><strong><br/>3. Freebies</strong></p><p>Additional campaign-themed items included along with your Project 01 delivery.</p><p>These can be:</p><ul><li>created exclusively for the Ludic Kitchen community</li><li>designed specifically for this Campaign</li><li>available for separate purchase</li></ul><p>Freebies are intended as small collectibles or fun additions that complement the main product. They do not affect the functionality or value of the primary product.</p><p>The quantity of freebies varies by tier:</p><ul><li><strong>Limited</strong> – a small number of inserts or extras</li><li><strong>Few More</strong> – a broader selection compared to the Taster tier</li><li><strong>A Lot More</strong> – the highest quantity and variety of inserts available in this Campaign</li></ul><p>These labels indicate <strong>relative differences between tiers</strong>, not fixed counts of items.</p><p>Exact contents, designs, and quantities may vary based on availability, production feasibility, and final packaging decisions. Specific details may be shared closer to fulfillment.</p><h3><strong>4. Stickers</strong></h3><p>A small set of campaign-themed stickers included with your delivery.</p><p>These are:</p><ul><li>decorative collectibles</li><li>designed specifically for Project 01</li><li>intended as fun keepsakes</li></ul><p>Sticker designs, sizes, and quantities may vary by Campaign and packaging constraints.</p><p>Stickers are optional add-ons and do not affect the functionality or value of the main product.</p><h3><strong>5. Early Product Access</strong></h3><p>Priority access to selected future Ludic product releases before they are made available to the general public.</p><p>This may include:</p><ul><li>early purchase windows</li><li>pre-launch ordering access</li><li>or advance notifications for upcoming drops</li></ul><p>Early access is intended to give contributors the opportunity to explore and purchase new Ludic products ahead of public release.</p><p>Access applies to eligible Ludic releases and may vary based on:</p><ul><li>product type</li><li>stock availability</li><li>launch plans</li><li>or operational constraints</li></ul><p>Not all products or collaborations may be included.</p><p>Specific details for each release will be communicated at the time of launch.</p><h3><strong>6. Ludic Credit</strong></h3><p>Ludic Credit is store credit issued to eligible contributors after the Campaign concludes.</p><p>It functions like prepaid purchase value that can be used for future orders on Ludic’s official platform.</p><p>Depending on your tier, you may receive:</p><ul><li><strong>Sous Chef:</strong> ₹5,000 (valid for 6 months)</li><li><strong>Head Chef:</strong> ₹10,000 (valid for 12 months)</li></ul><p>Credit is issued after Campaign Close and is independent of product delivery timelines.</p><p>Ludic Credit:</p><ul><li>can be used only for purchases within the Ludic ecosystem</li><li>must be redeemed in <strong>a single transaction</strong> (partial or split usage is not permitted)</li><li>cannot be withdrawn as cash</li><li>cannot be transferred or sold</li><li>does not earn interest</li></ul><p>If the credit is not redeemed within the validity period, it will expire automatically and cannot be reinstated or refunded.</p><p>All detailed issuance and usage rules are governed by the Ludic Credit Policy.</p><h3><strong>7. Additional Discount</strong></h3><p>An additional percentage-based discount applicable to eligible future purchases made on Ludic’s official platform.</p><p>This benefit is available exclusively to Kitchen contributors for a limited time after the Campaign concludes.</p><p>Depending on your tier, you may receive:</p><ul><li><strong>Sous Chef:</strong> 5% discount (valid for 6 months)</li><li><strong>Head Chef:</strong> 10% discount (valid for 6 months)</li></ul><p>The discount:</p><ul><li>may be used on <strong>multiple orders during the validity period</strong></li><li>is not limited to a single purchase</li><li>applies only to eligible Ludic products</li><li>may be applied automatically or via a code, as communicated at the time of purchase</li><li>may not be combinable with certain other offers or sale pricing</li><li>has no cash value</li><li>cannot be transferred to another account</li></ul><p>The discount expires automatically at the end of the validity period.</p><p>Specific applicability may vary by product or launch.</p><h3><strong>8. Certificate of Co-Creation</strong></h3><p>A certificate issued after Project 01 is completed to acknowledge your participation in the Campaign.</p><p>Depending on tier, this may be:</p><ul><li>a downloadable digital certificate, or</li><li>a digital certificate along with a printed physical copy included in your shipment</li></ul><p>The certificate typically includes:</p><ul><li>your name (or account name)</li><li>the Campaign name</li><li>confirmation of participation</li></ul><p>It serves as a commemorative acknowledgement only.</p><p>It does <strong>not</strong>:</p><ul><li>represent ownership in the product or brand</li><li>create equity, partnership, or financial rights</li><li>function as a legal document or contract</li></ul><h3><strong>9. Kitchen Ledger Access</strong></h3><p>Access to a digital transparency dashboard provided during the Campaign lifecycle.</p><p>The Ledger is intended to give contributors visibility into how the project is progressing.</p><p>It may include updates such as:</p><ul><li>major milestones</li><li>design progress</li><li>development stages</li><li>production status</li><li>key timeline checkpoints</li></ul><p>The Ledger is informational only.</p><p>It does <strong>not</strong> guarantee:</p><ul><li>real-time updates</li><li>daily reporting</li><li>disclosure of confidential or commercially sensitive information</li></ul><p>The type, depth, and frequency of updates are determined by Ludic based on operational feasibility.</p><h3><strong>10. Kitchen Archive Access</strong></h3><p>Digital access to selected materials from the design and development process.</p><p>This may include:</p><ul><li>early sketches</li><li>mock-ups</li><li>alternative concepts</li><li>rejected designs</li><li>experimental samples</li></ul><p>The Archive is curated and intended to provide insight into how decisions were made.</p><p>It does <strong>not</strong> represent a complete record of all internal work.</p><p>Ludic may choose which materials are shared and which remain internal.</p><p>Content may be added or removed over time.</p><h3><strong>11. Voting Rights</strong></h3><p>Opportunity to participate in selected polls or feedback sessions during the Campaign.</p><p>These votes may relate to areas such as:</p><ul><li>design direction</li><li>colours</li><li>features</li><li>styling elements</li></ul><p>Depending on tier:</p><ul><li><strong>Few Rights</strong> – access to a limited number of selected polls</li><li><strong>All Rights</strong> – access to most or all available polls<br/><br/></li></ul><p>Voting is advisory only.</p><p>This means:</p><ul><li>results help guide direction</li><li>results are considered during decision-making</li><li>but they are not binding</li></ul><p>Final decisions remain with Ludic based on feasibility, cost, quality, timelines, and manufacturing constraints.</p><p>A voting outcome does <strong>not</strong> guarantee that any specific option will be produced.</p><h3><strong>12. Exclusive DIY Kit</strong></h3><p>A physical kit provided to encourage deeper, hands-on engagement with the Campaign.</p><p>The kit may include:</p><ul><li>accessories</li><li>modular components</li><li>decorative elements</li><li>or creative materials related to the product</li></ul><p>Contents vary by Campaign and are not standardized.</p><p>The kit is supplementary.</p><p>It is not required for normal product use and does not affect core functionality.</p><h3><strong>13. Ludic Design Journal</strong></h3><p>A specially designed printed journal created exclusively for the Ludic Kitchen community as part of Project 01.</p><p>The journal is a fun, creative, and collectible keepsake inspired by the Campaign and the Ludic Clogs theme.</p><p>It may include:</p><ul><li>illustrated or playful pages</li><li>themed graphics and artwork</li><li>prompts or interactive sections</li><li>blank or lightly guided pages for notes, sketches, or ideas</li><li>campaign-inspired elements and storytelling</li></ul><p>The journal is intended for personal use as a planner, notebook, or creative companion.</p><p>It is not:</p><ul><li>a technical document</li><li>a product manual</li><li>or an instructional guide related to product usage</li></ul><p>Design, layout, and content may vary by Campaign and may differ slightly from previews.</p><h3><strong>14. Campaign Feature</strong></h3><p>Public acknowledgement of your participation as part of Project 01’s story.</p><p>This may include:</p><ul><li>listing your name</li><li>contributor credits</li><li>or inclusion in selected campaign-related content</li></ul><p>The form of acknowledgement may vary, including digital or printed formats.</p><p>Inclusion depends on:</p><ul><li>space</li><li>editorial planning</li><li>creative direction</li></ul><p>Feature placement is determined at Ludic’s discretion.</p><p>Inclusion is not guaranteed for every eligible contributor.</p><h3><strong>15. New Product Ideas</strong></h3><p>Opportunity to submit suggestions or ideas for future Ludic products or campaigns.</p><p>Ideas may be submitted through designated forms, emails, or community channels.</p><p>Submissions may be reviewed internally and may help inform future exploration.</p><p>However:</p><ul><li>submission does not guarantee implementation</li><li>no compensation is provided</li><li>no ownership or intellectual property rights are transferred to the contributor</li><li>no partnership or contractual relationship is created</li></ul><p>Ludic retains full discretion over whether and how ideas are used.</p><h3><strong>16. Exclusive Event Gatherings</strong></h3><p>Invite-only gatherings organised for contributors to connect with the Ludic team and community.</p><p>These may include:</p><ul><li>in-person meetups</li><li>workshops</li><li>launch events</li><li>or online sessions</li></ul><p>Events may be limited by:</p><ul><li>city or location</li><li>capacity</li><li>scheduling</li><li>operational constraints</li></ul><p>Invites may be limited or prioritised based on logistics.</p><p>Attendance is not guaranteed for all contributors.</p><p>Travel or accommodation costs, if any, are typically not covered unless explicitly stated.</p><h3><strong>17. Limited Edition Custom Colorway</strong></h3><p>A colourway or design variation created specifically for Kitchen contributors.</p><p>This version:</p><ul><li>is not offered in general retail at the time of launch</li><li>is available only to eligible tiers</li></ul><p>The colourway may include differences in:</p><ul><li>colour</li><li>finish</li><li>detailing</li><li>materials</li></ul><p>Final execution may vary slightly from previews or renders due to manufacturing or material constraints.</p><p>Availability may be limited based on production capacity.</p><h1><strong>7. Tier Benefits Overview</strong></h1><p>Each tier includes a different combination of perks and benefits.</p><p>The table below shows which perks are included with each tier.<br/> Detailed explanations of each perk are provided in the <strong>Perks & Rewards</strong> section above.</p><p><strong>Tier Comparison</strong></p><p><strong>Taster Tier</strong></p><p>Includes Ludic Clogs (product), recipe card, stickers, early access, and freebies(limited).</p><h3><strong>Sous Chef Tier</strong></h3><p>Includes Ludic Clogs (product), recipe card, stickers, early access, freebies (a few more), ₹5,000 Ludic Credit (6-month validity), 5% discount (6-month validity)(multi-use), digital certificate of co-creation, kitchen ledger and archive access, and few voting rights.</p><h3><strong>Head Chef Tier</strong></h3><p>Includes Ludic Clogs (product), recipe card, stickers, early access, freebies (a lot more) , ₹10,000 Ludic Credit (12-month validity), 10% discount (6-month validity)(multi-use), digital + print certificate of co-creation, all voting rights (within campaign scope), exclusive DIY kit, Ludic design journal, eligibility for campaign feature, new product ideas submission, invite to exclusive event gatherings, and limited edition custom colorway.</p><h2><strong>Notes</strong></h2><ul><li>“Limited / Few More / A Lot More” refers to relative quantity differences as explained in the Perks section.</li><li>Credit, discounts, and access benefits are subject to their respective validity periods and usage rules.</li><li>Perks are campaign-specific and may vary in future Ludic Kitchen projects.</li></ul><h1><strong>8. Activation & Production Framework</strong></h1><p>Project 01 follows a community-backed activation model.</p><p>This means production begins only if the Campaign reaches the required funding threshold.</p><h2><strong>8.1 Funding Structure</strong></h2><p>The funding structure for Project 01 is as follows:</p><ul><li><strong>Total Project Cost:</strong> ₹75,00,000</li><li><strong>Ludic Contribution (Brand Pledge):</strong> ₹15,00,000</li><li><strong>Community Target:</strong> ₹60,00,000</li></ul><p>The Community Target represents the amount required from contributors to activate production.</p><h2><strong>8.2 Activation Threshold</strong></h2><p>The Campaign is considered <strong>Activated</strong> once 75% of the Community Target is reached.</p><p>For Project 01:</p><ul><li>75% of ₹60,00,000 = ₹45,00,000</li></ul><p>Once this threshold is met:</p><ul><li>The project is approved for production</li><li>Manufacturing and sourcing processes begin</li><li>Contributors remain eligible for all selected perks</li></ul><p>Activation does not end the Campaign.<br/>The Campaign continues for the full 60-day duration.</p><h2><strong>8.3 Brand Top-Up Window (70–74%)</strong></h2><p>If the Campaign reaches between 70% and 74% of the Community Target, Ludic may, at its sole discretion, choose to top up the remaining amount to activate the project.</p><p>This decision is based on:</p><ul><li>operational feasibility</li><li>production viability</li><li>strategic considerations</li></ul><p>Brand top-up is not guaranteed.</p><h2><strong>8.4 Non-Activation</strong></h2><p>If the Campaign closes below 70% of the Community Target:</p><ul><li>The project will not proceed to production.</li><li>Contributions will be handled as per the Refund Policy.</li></ul><p>No product will be manufactured in this case.</p><h2><strong>8.5 Production Start & Timeline</strong></h2><p>Production begins only after Activation.</p><p>Estimated fulfillment timeline:</p><ul><li>8–10 weeks after Campaign Close</li></ul><p>Timelines are estimates and may vary due to:</p><ul><li>manufacturing constraints</li><li>material sourcing</li><li>logistics</li><li>unforeseen operational factors</li></ul><p>Contributors will receive updates through the Kitchen Ledger and official communication channels.</p><h1><strong>9. Production, Fulfillment & Delivery</strong></h1><p>Once the Campaign is Activated, Ludic begins production and fulfillment of the Ludic Kitchen Product and associated perks.</p><h2><strong>9.1 Production Timeline</strong></h2><p>Production starts only after Activation and after the Campaign closes.</p><p>For Project 01:</p><ul><li>Estimated fulfillment timeline: <strong>8–10 weeks after Campaign Close</strong></li></ul><p>This includes:</p><ul><li>manufacturing</li><li>quality checks</li><li>packaging</li><li>perk assembly</li><li>dispatch preparation</li></ul><p>All timelines are estimates and may vary depending on operational or supply chain factors.</p><h2><strong>9.2 Order Processing</strong></h2><p>Each confirmed Seat is treated as one fulfillment unit.</p><p>Your shipment may include:</p><ul><li>the Ludic Kitchen Product</li><li>physical inserts and collectibles</li><li>any applicable tier-specific physical perks</li></ul><p>Digital perks (such as certificates, ledger access, archive access, credits, or discounts) may be delivered separately via email or account access and may not be part of the physical shipment.</p><h2><strong>9.3 Dispatch & Delivery</strong></h2><p>Orders will be dispatched once ready.</p><p>Delivery timelines after dispatch depend on:</p><ul><li>shipping partner</li><li>serviceability of your location</li><li>local logistics conditions</li></ul><p>Tracking details will be shared where available.</p><h2><strong>9.4 Batch Fulfillment</strong></h2><p>Orders may be fulfilled in batches rather than all at once.</p><p>This means:</p><ul><li>different contributors may receive shipments at different times</li><li>higher tiers or specific variants may ship earlier or later depending on packaging and inventory readiness</li></ul><p>Batch dispatch helps ensure smoother operations and faster overall fulfillment.</p><h2><strong>9.5 Delays</strong></h2><p>While Ludic aims to meet estimated timelines, delays may occur due to factors outside our direct control, including:</p><ul><li>manufacturing or vendor delays</li><li>material shortages</li><li>quality issues</li><li>customs or logistics disruptions</li><li>force majeure events</li></ul><p>Such delays do not qualify for refunds, cancellations, or compensation.</p><p>Contributors will be kept informed through official updates.</p><h2><strong>9.6 Address Accuracy</strong></h2><p>Contributors are responsible for providing accurate shipping details.</p><p>Ludic is not responsible for failed deliveries caused by:</p><ul><li>incorrect or incomplete addresses</li><li>unreachable recipients</li><li>repeated delivery failures</li></ul><p>Additional shipping charges may apply for re-dispatch where required.</p><h2><strong>9.7 Multiple Shipments</strong></h2><p>In some cases:</p><ul><li>physical perks and product may ship separately, or</li><li>digital perks may be issued at different times</li></ul><p>This does not affect your eligibility for any included benefits.</p><h2><strong>9.8 Nature of Estimates</strong></h2><p>All delivery and production timelines shared during the Campaign are <strong>estimates</strong>, not guaranteed dates.</p><p>By participating, contributors acknowledge that Ludic Kitchen follows a build-after-backing model, and timelines may shift as the product is created.</p><h1><strong>10. Campaign Changes & Operational Adjustments</strong></h1><p>Ludic Kitchen is a build-in-public, evolving creation process.</p><p>Because products and perks are developed after the Campaign begins, certain operational or logistical adjustments may be required during the lifecycle of the project.</p><h2><strong>10.1 Nature of the Process</strong></h2><p>Contributors acknowledge that:</p><ul><li>designs evolve</li><li>prototypes improve</li><li>materials may change</li><li>production decisions may be refined</li></ul><p>These changes are part of the normal development process and are made to improve quality, feasibility, or delivery.</p><p>Final products and perks may differ slightly from early visuals, mock-ups, or descriptions shared during the Campaign.</p><h2><strong>10.2 Permitted Adjustments</strong></h2><p>Ludic may make reasonable operational changes, including but not limited to:</p><ul><li>packaging or insert updates</li><li>substitutions of freebies or minor perks</li><li>vendor or manufacturing changes</li><li>timeline adjustments</li><li>sequencing of dispatch</li><li>format changes (digital vs physical)</li><li>event rescheduling or cancellation</li><li>design refinements that do not materially alter core functionality</li></ul><p>Such changes are made to ensure smooth execution and overall project quality.</p><h2><strong>10.3 Perk Substitutions</strong></h2><p>If a specific perk, insert, or component becomes unavailable due to production or supply constraints, Ludic may:</p><ul><li>modify the design, or</li><li>replace it with a similar item of comparable intent or value</li></ul><p>This does not affect your eligibility for the main product or core tier benefits.</p><h2><strong>10.4 No Material Reduction</strong></h2><p>Any adjustments will not materially reduce:</p><ul><li>the primary product promised</li><li>the core value of the selected tier</li></ul><p>Ludic will make reasonable efforts to maintain the overall experience and benefit of participation.</p><h2><strong>10.5 Communication</strong></h2><p>Where meaningful changes occur, Ludic will share updates through:</p><ul><li>official email communication</li><li>the Kitchen Ledger</li></ul><p>so contributors remain informed.</p><h1><strong>11. Support & Communication</strong></h1><p>Ludic aims to keep the Ludic Kitchen process transparent and responsive for all contributors.</p><p>If you have questions, concerns, or need assistance related to your participation in Project 01, you may contact us through the official support channels below.</p><h2><strong>11.1 Contact</strong></h2><p>For all Campaign-related queries, please reach out to:</p><p><strong>Email:</strong> kitchen@ludic.life</p><h2><strong>11.2 Response Time</strong></h2><p>We aim to respond to most queries within:</p><ul><li>2–3 business days</li></ul><p>Response times may be longer during:</p><ul><li>Campaign launch</li><li>Campaign close</li><li>dispatch periods</li><li>or peak volumes</li></ul><p>We appreciate your patience during these windows.</p><h2><strong>11.3 Official Communication Channels</strong></h2><p>Important updates regarding the Campaign may be shared through:</p><ul><li>email</li><li>the Ludic Kitchen Ledger</li><li>or official Ludic social/website announcements</li></ul><p>Contributors are encouraged to check these channels periodically for updates on production, fulfillment, and timelines.</p><h2><strong>11.4 Scope of Support</strong></h2><p>Our team can assist with:</p><ul><li>order confirmation</li><li>address updates (before dispatch)</li><li>delivery issues</li><li>credit issuance</li><li>perk clarification</li><li>general Campaign questions</li></ul><p>Requests that conflict with these Campaign Terms, the Refund Policy, or the Credit Policy may not be accommodated.</p><h1><strong>12. Relationship to Master Terms & Acceptance</strong></h1><p>These Campaign Terms apply specifically to <strong>Ludic Kitchen — Project 01: Ludic Clogs</strong> and outline the operational structure, timelines, tiers, and perks for this Campaign.</p><p>They should be read together with Ludic’s:</p><ul><li>Master Terms of Use</li><li>Refund Policy</li><li>Credit Policy</li><li>Privacy Policy</li></ul><p>All of the above policies apply in addition to these Campaign Terms.</p><p>In the event of any conflict:</p><ul><li>these Campaign Terms will govern matters specific to this Campaign</li><li>the Master Terms & Policies will govern all other legal, transactional, and platform-related matters</li></ul><p>By selecting a tier and completing your contribution, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agreed to these Campaign Terms and the associated policies.</p>"
